Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Henley upon 
    Thames. Abolished 1.4.1952 and divided between the parishes of Bix and Rotherfield 
    Greys.

Renamed 22.7.1986 to become the parish of Bix & Assendon. See 
    also Table 2, note (f).

Created 22.7.1986 by renaming the parish of Bix. See also Table 2, note 
    (j).

Created 1.10.1912 from the parishes of Britwell Salome and Britwell 
    Prior. See also Table 2, note (e).
Abolished 1.10.1912 and added to the parish of Britwell.
Abolished 1.10.1912 and added to the parish of Britwell.

Abolished 1.4.1932 and added to the parish of Cuxham with 
    Easington. See also Table 2, note (e).

That part which until 1.4.1932 formed the parish of Cuxham. 
    See also Table 2, note (e).

Created 1.4.1952 out of the parishes of Goring and Whitchurch. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Rotherfield Greys 
    in Henley upon Thames Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.10.1905 and added to the parish of Henley upon Thames.

Created 1.4.1952 out of the parish of Rotherfield Greys. See also 
    Table 2, note (j).

Created 1894 from the rural part of the parish of Caversham. Renamed 
    31.3.1902 to become the parish of Kidmore End.

Created 31.3.1902 by renaming the parish of Kidmore. See also 
    Table 2, notes (h) and (j).

Abolished 1.10.1922 and added to the parish of Pishill with 
    Stonor.

Created 1.10.1922 from the separate parishes of Stonor and Pishill. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).
Created 1.4.1952 out of the parishes of Eye & Dunsden, Shiplake and Kidmore End. See also Table 2, note (j).

Created 1.4.1952 out of the parishes of Crowmarsh and Ipsden. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).

Created 1.10.1896 out of the parish of Pyrton. Abolished 1.10.1922 
    and added to the parish of Pishill with Stonor.

Renamed 15.12.1992 to become the parish of 
    Whitchurch on Thames. See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 15.12.1992 by renaming the parish of Whitchurch. See 
    also Table 2, note (j).

Created 1.4.1952 out of the parishes of South Stoke and Goring. 
    See also Table 2, note (j).
